I just don't feel right doing it. I've lost streaks because of it, but I feel better doing it the way I do.

@Jack McCullough, and that's the beauty of it; we each can set our own standard. I tend to take several run-throughs before considering help. First line of defense is the tricky clues section of the column, and I only reveal them one at a time. Once I use a hint, I see if it advances my cause before looking at the next one! Sadly for me, my brain isn't often on the same wavelength as our incredible columnists; the suggested tricky clues aren't often the ones I'm struggling with.  🤷🏼‍♀️😂

I may resort to Google but generally only on Friday or Saturday.

It's complicated, I know, but it works for me!

