@sonnel

With my first name being a nickname and having blithely flip-flopped early in our marriage between my maiden name, married name, and a hyphenated name—and let’s not forget all the limited-character-number online forms common back in the 00’s which frequently randomly truncated long names—I’ve ended up with different versions of myself on my driver’s license, passport, birth certificate, marriage certificate, and various accounts. 

